            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.29-31_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">29</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS
                        <lb/>
                    1030 FIFTH AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK 28</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>September 2, 1955</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Professor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route No. 6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Professor Neihardt</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your recent re-election to succeed yourself once again completes the Board of Chancellors, a list of which is enclosed.</p>
                
                <p>The Board of Directors has instructed me to advise you that $5,000. is now available for a Fellowship. Procedure will be similar to that followed in connection with the last award.</p>
                
                <p>Your attention is directed to Article VIII of our Charter which prescribes the qualifications of Fellows as follows: "poets of proven merit either natural-born or naturalized American citizens."</p>
                
                <p>Under Article VI of the By-Laws, you are entitled to nominate two candidates for this Fellowship, but obviously you may limit your choice to one. A nominating slip is enclosed.</p>
                
                <p>It would be helpful if you would indicate thereon briefly the reasons which motivate your nominations. The By-Laws require that the Chancellors be notified of the names of all such nominees and of their nominators respectively, although, when voting begins, the signed ballots will be kept confidential by the Secretary.</p>
                
                <p>It will be remembered that the following previous awards of $5,000. have been made: Edwin Markham, 1937; Edgar Lee Masters, 1946; Ridgely Torrence, 1947; Percy MacKaye, 1948; <hi rend="caps">E. E.</hi> Cummings, 1950; Padraic Colum, 1952; Robert Frost, 1953; Louise Townsend Nicholl, 1954; Oliver St. John Gogarty, 1954.</p>
                
                <p>The closing date for these nominations has been set for October 3, 1955.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Hugh Bullock
                    Secretary</signed>
                    
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">Enclosures</note>
               
